# Kubernetes Operators-specific secure coding rules for Cursor
# This file provides security best practices for Kubernetes Operator projects.
---
description: Secure coding rules for Kubernetes Operators ⚙️
globs:
  - "**/operator*"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Minimize cluster and namespace permissions; avoid cluster-admin and wildcards.
- Deploy operators in separate namespaces and avoid shared namespaces.
- Set readOnlyRootFilesystem and runAsNonRoot to true.
